<eesti>Puhkuseseadus </eesti>
<inglise>Holidays Act </inglise>
<eesti>Vastu v&otilde;etud 4. aprillil 2001. a. </eesti>
<inglise>Passed 4 April 2001 </inglise>
<eesti>(RT I 2001, 42, 233), </eesti>
<inglise>(RT (1) I 2001, 42, 233), </inglise>
<eesti>j&otilde;ustunud 1. jaanuaril 2002. a. </eesti>
<inglise>entered into force 1 January 2002. </inglise>
<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev seadus s&auml;testab t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tavate isikute ja avalike teenistujate (edaspidi t&ouml;&ouml;taja) puhkuse kestuse ning korralduse alused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act provides the duration of holidays and bases for the organisation of grant of holidays to persons working on the basis of employment contracts and to public servants (hereinafter employees). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevat seadust ei kohaldata t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele, kelle puhkus on reguleeritud muude seadustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act does not apply to employees whose holidays are regulated by other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse m&otilde;iste ja liigid </eesti>
<inglise>Definition and classification of holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Puhkus t&auml;hendab t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu v&otilde;i teenistussuhte peatumist k&auml;esoleva seadusega etten&auml;htud korras ja tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A holiday means the suspension of an employment contract or a service relationship pursuant to the procedure and under the conditions prescribed in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml; iseloomu ja tingimuste j&auml;rgi antavad puhkused on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Holidays granted according to the nature of the work and working conditions are the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&otilde;hipuhkus, sealhulgas pikendatud puhkus vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 9; </eesti>
<inglise>1) annual holiday, including extended holiday pursuant to &sect; 9 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) lisapuhkus vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 10. </eesti>
<inglise>2) additional holiday pursuant to &sect; 10 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud puhkustele on k&auml;esoleva seaduse reguleerimisobjektiks: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In addition to the holidays specified in subsection 2 of this section, this Act regulates: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vanemapuhkused vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-dele 27-31; </eesti>
<inglise>1) leave for parents pursuant to &sect;&sect; 27-31 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) palgata puhkus vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-dele 32-35. </eesti>
<inglise>2) holiday without pay pursuant to &sect;&sect; 32-35 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmine t&ouml;&ouml;aasta eest </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of holidays for working year </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hi- ja lisapuhkust, samuti t&auml;iendavat lapsepuhkust vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 30 (v&auml;lja arvatud &sect; 30 l&otilde;ike 1 alusel antav puhkus) antakse t&ouml;&ouml;aasta eest. </eesti>
<inglise>Annual holiday, additional holiday and additional child care leave pursuant to &sect; 30 of this Act, (except the holiday granted pursuant to subsection 30 (1)) shall be granted per working year. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aasta on aeg, mis algab selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures t&ouml;&ouml;le asumise p&auml;evast ja kestab j&auml;rgmise aasta sama p&auml;evani. </eesti>
<inglise>A working year is a year which commences on the day a person commences work with an employer and continues until the same day of the following year. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui selles ajavahemikus on perioode, mida vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 4 t&ouml;&ouml;aasta hulka ei arvata, l&uuml;kkub t&ouml;&ouml;aasta l&otilde;pp vastava arvu p&auml;evade v&otilde;rra edasi. </eesti>
<inglise>If there are periods of time which are not included in the working year pursuant to &sect; 4 of this Act, the end of the working year shall be postponed by the corresponding number of days. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aastast l&uuml;hema aja eest antakse puhkust v&otilde;rdeliselt t&ouml;&ouml;tatud ajaga. </eesti>
<inglise>For periods shorter than a working year, holidays shall be granted in proportion to the amount of time worked. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aasta arvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of working year </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lisaks tegelikult t&ouml;&ouml;tatud ajale arvatakse t&ouml;&ouml;aasta hulka: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In addition to actual time worked, a working year shall include: </inglise>
<eesti>1) aeg, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) periods during which an employee is temporarily incapacitated for work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) puhkuse aeg, v&auml;lja arvatud lapsehoolduspuhkuse ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja soovil antud palgata puhkuse aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>2) holidays, except parental leave and holidays without pay granted at the request of the employee; </inglise>
<eesti>3) osaliselt tasustatava puhkuse aeg vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 33; </eesti>
<inglise>3) holidays with partial pay pursuant to &sect; 33 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu ebaseadusliku l&otilde;petamise, ebaseaduslikult teenistusest vabastamise v&otilde;i ebaseaduslikult teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimise t&otilde;ttu t&ouml;&ouml;lt sunnitud puudumise aeg, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja on t&ouml;&ouml;le ennistatud; </eesti>
<inglise>4) periods of forced absence from work due to unlawful termination of employment contract, unlawful release from service or unlawful transfer to other work, if the employee is reinstated to employment; </inglise>
<eesti>5) muu aeg, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on seaduse, muu &otilde;igusakti, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga etten&auml;htud alustel ajutiselt vabastatud t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>5) other periods during which an employee is temporarily released from performance of his or her duties on the bases prescribed by law, other legislation, a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja otsusega v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;aasta hulka arvata ka muu aja, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on poolte kokkuleppel ajutiselt vabastatud t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) By a decision of the employer, other periods during which an employee is temporarily released from performance of his or her duties by agreement of the parties may also be included in a working year. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse kestuse arvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of duration of holiday </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse kestust arvutatakse, olenemata t&ouml;&ouml;ajakorraldusest t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures, kalendrip&auml;evades, mille hulka ei arvata rahvusp&uuml;ha ja riigip&uuml;hi. </eesti>
<inglise>Regardless of the organisation of working time with an employer, the duration of a holiday shall be calculated in calendar days, and does not include national holidays and public holidays. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse pikendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Extension of holiday </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale seaduse v&otilde;i muu &otilde;igusaktiga etten&auml;htud puhkust v&otilde;ib pikendada kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga, samuti poolte kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>A holiday prescribed for an employee by law or other legislation may be extended by a collective agreement or employment contract, or by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmise kohustus ning puhkusest loobumise kehtetus </eesti>
<inglise>Duty to grant holiday and invalidity of waived holiday </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andjal ei ole &otilde;igust j&auml;tta puhkust andmata ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajal ei ole &otilde;igust puhkusest loobuda. </eesti>
<inglise>Employers do not have the right to withhold holidays and employees do not have the right to waive holidays. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusen&otilde;ude aegumine </eesti>
<inglise>Expiry of claim for entitlement to holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Puhkusen&otilde;ude &otilde;igus kehtib kuni nelja viimase aasta eest antavale puhkusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The right of claim for entitlement to holiday applies to holidays to be granted for the last four years. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Puhkuse kasutamist takistavate asjaolude tekkimisel hakkab kasutamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkuse osa aegumist&auml;htaeg kulgema p&auml;rast takistavate asjaolude &auml;ralangemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If circumstances hindering the use of a holiday arise, the limitation period for the portion of the holiday that is not used starts to run after the hindering circumstances cease to exist. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hi- ja lisapuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Annual Holiday and Additional Holiday </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hipuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Annual holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&otilde;hipuhkuse kestus on 28 kalendrip&auml;eva, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The duration of an annual holiday is twenty-eight calendar days, except in the cases prescribed in subsections (2) and (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pikendatud p&otilde;hipuhkust antakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An extended annual holiday shall be granted to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) alaealistele 35 kalendrip&auml;eva; </eesti>
<inglise>1) minors, thirty-five calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isikutele, kellele on m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension v&otilde;i rahvapension t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse alusel vastavalt riikliku pensionikindlustuse seadusele (RT I 1998, 64/65, 1009; 2001, 9, 42), 35 kalendrip&auml;eva; </eesti>
<inglise>2) persons who are granted a pension for incapacity for work or the national pension on the basis of incapacity for work pursuant to the State Pension Insurance Act (RT I 1998, 64/65, 1009; 2001, 9, 42), thirty-five calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riigi- ja kohaliku omavalitsuse ametnikele 35 kalendrip&auml;eva; </eesti>
<inglise>3) state officials and local government officials, thirty-five calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>4) koolieelsete lasteasutuste, lasteaed-algkoolide, algkoolide, p&otilde;hikoolide ja g&uuml;mnaasiumide, huvialakoolide, kutse&otilde;ppeasutuste, rakendusk&otilde;rgkoolide, &uuml;likoolide ning teadus- ja arendusasutuste juhtidele, &otilde;petajatele, &otilde;ppej&otilde;ududele ja teistele pedagoogidele ning teadust&ouml;&ouml;tajatele kuni 56 kalendrip&auml;eva; </eesti>
<inglise>4) heads, teachers, academic staff, and other pedagogical specialists and scientific staff of pre-school child care institutions, nursery-primary schools, primary schools, basic schools and upper secondary schools, hobby schools, vocational educational institutions, institutions of applied higher education, universities and research and development institutions, up to fifty-six calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>5) raviasutuste, sotsiaalhoolekandeasutuste ja lastesanatooriumide pedagoogikaspetsialistidele kuni 56 kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>5) pedagogical specialists of medical institutions, social welfare institutions and children's sanatoriums, up to fifty-six calendar days. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametikohtade loetelu, kus t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel antakse pikendatud puhkust kuni 56 kalendrip&auml;eva, ja puhkuse kestuse konkreetsel ametikohal kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A list of positions where extended holidays are granted for up to fifty-six calendar days and the duration of holidays for particular positions shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Osalise t&ouml;&ouml;ajaga t&ouml;&ouml;taja p&otilde;hipuhkus on sama kestusega kui t&auml;ist&ouml;&ouml;ajaga t&ouml;&ouml;tajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The annual holiday of an employee who works part-time shall be of the same duration as the annual holiday of a full-time employee. </inglise>
<eesti>Osalise t&ouml;&ouml;ajaga t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel v&otilde;ib lisapuhkuse kestust l&uuml;hendada ainult seadusega etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of part-time employment, the duration of an additional holiday may be shortened only in the cases prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahviga etten&auml;htud puhkuse kestust ei kohaldata t&ouml;&ouml;tajate suhtes, kelle puhkus on reguleeritud eri seadusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The duration of holidays prescribed in this section is not applicable to employees whose holidays are regulated by a specific Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisapuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Additional holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;igus lisapuhkusele on t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employees have the right to an additional holiday if they are engaged in: </inglise>
<eesti>1) allmaat&ouml;&ouml;del; </eesti>
<inglise>1) underground work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tervistkahjustavatel t&ouml;&ouml;del; </eesti>
<inglise>2) work which poses a health hazard; </inglise>
<eesti>3) eriiseloomuga t&ouml;&ouml;del. </eesti>
<inglise>3) work of a special nature. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Allmaat&ouml;&ouml;de, tervistkahjustavate t&ouml;&ouml;de ja eriiseloomuga t&ouml;&ouml;de loetelu, kus t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel antakse lisapuhkust, ning nende lisapuhkuste kestuse kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A list of underground work, work which poses a health hazard and work of a special nature where an additional holiday is granted, and the duration of the additional holiday shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kollektiiv- ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga v&otilde;ib ette n&auml;ha t&auml;iendavad alused lisapuhkuse andmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Supplementary bases for granting an additional holiday may be prescribed by a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teiste seadustega v&otilde;ib ette n&auml;ha ka muid lisapuhkusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Other additional holidays may be prescribed by other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisapuhkuse andmise tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions for granting additional holiday </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kellele antakse p&otilde;hipuhkus t&auml;ies ulatuses enne t&ouml;&ouml;aasta t&auml;itumist, antakse koos p&otilde;hipuhkusega lisapuhkus samuti t&auml;ies ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>Employees who are granted an annual holiday in full before the end of a working year shall also be granted an additional holiday in full, together with the annual holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hi- ja lisapuhkuse liitmine </eesti>
<inglise>Combining annual holiday and additional holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lisapuhkus liidetakse p&otilde;hipuhkusele ja antakse sellega koos v&otilde;i poolte kokkuleppel muul ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An additional holiday shall be added to an annual holiday and shall be granted together with the annual holiday or, by agreement of the parties, at another time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Erinevatel alustel antavad lisapuhkused liidetakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Additional holidays granted on different bases shall be added together. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for Granting Holidays </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmine esimesel t&ouml;&ouml;aastal </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of holidays during first working year </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal, kes on esimesel t&ouml;&ouml;aastal t&ouml;&ouml;tanud v&auml;hemalt kuus kuud, on &otilde;igus saada puhkust v&otilde;rdeliselt t&ouml;&ouml;tatud kuude arvuga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employees who have worked at least six months during their first working year have the right to be granted a holiday in proportion to the number of months worked. </inglise>
<eesti>Saamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkuseosa antakse t&ouml;&ouml;aasta kestel m&otilde;nel muul ajal v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;usolekul liidetakse j&auml;rgmise t&ouml;&ouml;aasta puhkusega v&otilde;i antakse teise t&ouml;&ouml;aasta kestel m&otilde;nel muul ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>Portion of holiday which has not been received shall be granted during the working year at another time, shall be added to the holiday of the following working year with the consent of the employee, or shall be granted at another time during the second working year. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) S&otilde;ltumata t&ouml;&ouml;tatud ajast, on esimesel t&ouml;&ouml;aastal &otilde;igus saada puhkust t&auml;ies ulatuses: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Regardless of the amount of time worked, the following have the right to receive a holiday in full during the first working year: </inglise>
<eesti>1) alaealisel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) minors; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isikul, kellele on m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension v&otilde;i rahvapension t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse alusel vastavalt riikliku pensionikindlustuse seadusele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) persons who are granted a pension for incapacity for work or the national pension on the basis of incapacity for work pursuant to the State Pension Insurance Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) naisel enne v&otilde;i p&auml;rast rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkust; </eesti>
<inglise>3) women before or after pregnancy leave or maternity leave; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;ga seotud tervisekahjustuse j&auml;rgselt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime osaliselt kaotanud t&ouml;&ouml;tajal; </eesti>
<inglise>4) employees who are partially incapacitated for work due to a work-related injury; </inglise>
<eesti>5) muudel seaduse, muu &otilde;igusakti, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>5) in other cases prescribed by law, other legislation, a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib esimesel t&ouml;&ouml;aastal anda puhkust t&auml;ies ulatuses, s&otilde;ltumata t&ouml;&ouml;tatud ajast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) By agreement of the parties, a holiday may be granted in full during the first working year regardless of the amount of time worked. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmine teise ja j&auml;rgmiste t&ouml;&ouml;aastate eest </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of holidays for second and subsequent working years </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkust teise ja j&auml;rgmiste t&ouml;&ouml;aastate eest antakse t&auml;ies ulatuses t&ouml;&ouml;aasta kestel vastavalt t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures kehtivale puhkuste ajakavale. </eesti>
<inglise>Holidays shall be granted in full for the second or subsequent working years according to the holiday schedule of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib puhkuste ajakava muuta. </eesti>
<inglise>By agreement of the parties, a holiday schedule may be changed. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuste ajakava muutmisel tuleb m&auml;&auml;rata uus puhkuse aeg. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon changing the holiday schedule, a new holiday time shall be determined. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuste ajakava </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday schedule </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja koostab puhkuste ajakava iga kalendriaasta kohta ja teeb selle t&ouml;&ouml;tajale teatavaks jaanuarikuu jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers shall prepare a holiday schedule for every calendar year and communicate it to the employees during the month of January. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuste ajakava v&otilde;ib muuta poolte kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>By agreement of the parties, a holiday schedule may be changed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Puhkuste ajakava koostamisel l&auml;htub t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml; korraldamise huvidest, arvestades v&otilde;imaluse korral t&ouml;&ouml;tajate soove. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employers shall prepare a holiday schedule based on the interests of work management, taking requests of employees into consideration if possible. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud puhkuste ajakava koostamisel arvestama nende t&ouml;&ouml;tajate soovidega, kellel on vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 16 punktidele 3-6 &otilde;igus saada puhkust neile sobival ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon preparing a holiday schedule, employers are required to consider the requests of the employees who by law have the right to receive holidays at a time suitable for them pursuant to clauses 16 3) -6) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja ei tee puhkuste ajakava t&ouml;&ouml;tajale teatavaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 toodud t&auml;htaja jooksul, on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus j&auml;&auml;da puhkusele t&ouml;&ouml;taja poolt valitud ajal, teatades sellest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kirjalikult ette v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an employer does not communicate a holiday schedule to employees within the term specified in subsection (1) of this section, the employees have the right to take holiday at the time chosen by them and shall notify the employer thereof in writing at least two weeks in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmine t&ouml;&ouml;tajale sobival ajal </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of holidays at time suitable for employees </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja soovitud ajal on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud andma puhkust: </eesti>
<inglise>An employer is required to grant a holiday at the time requested by the employee to the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) naisele vahetult enne ja p&auml;rast rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkust v&otilde;i vahetult p&auml;rast lapsehoolduspuhkust; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a woman immediately before and after pregnancy leave or maternity leave or immediately after parental leave; </inglise>
<eesti>2) mehele vahetult p&auml;rast lapsehoolduspuhkust v&otilde;i naise rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkuse ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a man immediately after a parental leave or during pregnancy leave or maternity leave of his wife; </inglise>
<eesti>3) vanemale, kes kasvatab kuni 7-aastast last; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a parent raising a child of up to 7 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>4) vanemale, kes kasvatab 7-10-aastast last, - lapse koolivaheajal; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a parent raising a child of between 7 and 10 years of age, during a school holiday of the child; </inglise>
<eesti>5) alaealisele; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a minor; </inglise>
<eesti>6) t&ouml;&ouml;ga seotud tervisekahjustuse j&auml;rgselt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime osaliselt kaotanud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale. </eesti>
<inglise>6) an employee who is partially incapacitated for work due to a work-related injury. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse kasutamist takistavad asjaolud </eesti>
<inglise>Circumstances preventing employee from taking holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Puhkuse kasutamist takistavad asjaolud on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The circumstances preventing employee from taking holiday are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;taja ajutine t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) temporary incapacity for work of an employee; </inglise>
<eesti>2) rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkusel viibimine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) pregnancy leave or maternity leave; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsusorgani poolt pandud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) performance of duties assigned by a state or local government body; </inglise>
<eesti>4) osalemine seaduslikus streigis v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindamine kollektiivl&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimistel seadusega v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga etten&auml;htud korras; </eesti>
<inglise>4) participation in a lawful strike or representation of employees in collective bargaining pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law or a collective agreement; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &otilde;ppepuhkusel viibimine. </eesti>
<inglise>5) being on study leave. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;andjale teatama puhkuse kasutamist takistavatest asjaoludest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employees are required to inform the employer of circumstances which prevent them from taking a holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda puhkuse kasutamist takistavate asjaolude t&otilde;endamiseks dokumente. </eesti>
<inglise>The employer may demand documents which prove the circumstances which prevent an employee from taking the holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse v&otilde;i puhkuseosa &uuml;leviimine muule ajale seoses puhkuse kasutamist takistavate asjaoludega </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of holiday or portion of holiday to another time due to circumstances which prevent employee from taking holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui puhkuse kasutamist takistavad asjaolud vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 17 l&otilde;ike 1 punktidele 1-4 tekkisid enne puhkuse algust, viiakse puhkus &uuml;le poolte kokkuleppega m&auml;&auml;ratud ajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If circumstances which prevent an employee from taking a holiday pursuant to clauses 17 (1) 1) -4) of this Act arise before the beginning of the holiday, the holiday shall be transferred to a time determined by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui puhkuse kasutamist takistavad asjaolud tekkisid puhkuse ajal, antakse saamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkuseosa vahetult p&auml;rast takistavate asjaolude l&otilde;ppemist v&otilde;i viiakse poolte kokkuleppel &uuml;le muule ajale. </eesti>
<inglise>If circumstances which prevent an employee from taking a holiday arise during the holiday, the unused portion of holiday shall be granted immediately after such circumstances cease to exist, or shall be transferred to another time by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>Rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkuse t&otilde;ttu puhkuse &uuml;leviimisel teisele ajale kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 16 punkti 1. </eesti>
<inglise>Clause 16 1) of this Act applies upon the transfer of a holiday to another time due to pregnancy leave or maternity leave. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui pooled ei ole saavutanud kokkulepet saamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkuse v&otilde;i selle osa &uuml;leviimise kohta, on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus j&auml;&auml;da puhkusele saamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkusep&auml;evade ulatuses, teatades sellest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kirjalikult ette kaks n&auml;dalat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If parties have not reached an agreement on transfer of a holiday or a portion of the holiday which was not used, the employee has the right to take the holiday to the extent of the unused holiday days and shall notify the employer thereof in writing at least two weeks in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse &uuml;leviimine muule ajale poolte kokkuleppel </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of holiday to another time by agreement of parties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib puhkuse &uuml;le viia muule ajale samal t&ouml;&ouml;aastal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) By agreement of the parties, a holiday may be transferred to another time during the same working year. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui puhkuse &uuml;leviimist taotleb t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja kokkulepet t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga ei saavutata, on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus j&auml;&auml;da puhkusele puhkuste ajakavas etten&auml;htud ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>If an employer requests the transfer of a holiday but no agreement is reached with the employee, the employee has the right to take holiday at the time prescribed in the holiday schedule. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib osa puhkusest &uuml;le viia j&auml;rgmisele t&ouml;&ouml;aastale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) By agreement of the parties, a portion of a holiday may be transferred to the following working year. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;rgmisele t&ouml;&ouml;aastale &uuml;leviidud puhkuse osa liidetakse jooksva t&ouml;&ouml;aasta p&otilde;hipuhkusega v&otilde;i antakse poolte kokkuleppel m&otilde;nel muul ajal t&ouml;&ouml;aasta kestel. </eesti>
<inglise>A portion of a holiday transferred to the following working year shall be added to the annual holiday of the given working year or, by agreement of the parties, shall be granted at another time during the working year. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Alaealisele antakse puhkust igal t&ouml;&ouml;aastal t&auml;ies ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Minors shall be granted a holiday in full every working year. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse v&otilde;i selle osa &uuml;leviimine on lubatud vaid seoses rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkusel viibimisega. </eesti>
<inglise>The transfer of a holiday or a portion of a holiday is permitted only if the employee is on pregnancy leave or maternity leave. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmine osadena </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of holiday in parts </inglise>
<eesti>Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib puhkust anda osade kaupa, kusjuures &uuml;he katkestamatu osa kestus peab olema v&auml;hemalt 14 kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>By agreement of the parties, a holiday may be granted in parts; the duration of one continuous part must be at least fourteen calendar days. </inglise>
<eesti>Teiste puhkuseosade kestus v&otilde;ib olla l&uuml;hem. </eesti>
<inglise>The duration of other parts of the holiday may be shorter. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse katkestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Interruption of holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Puhkuse v&otilde;ib katkestada ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;le tagasi kutsuda poolte kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A holiday may be interrupted and an employee may be asked to return to work by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Puhkuse katkestamise t&otilde;ttu kasutamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkuse osa antakse poolte kokkuleppel sama t&ouml;&ouml;aasta m&otilde;nel muul ajal, liidetakse j&auml;rgmise t&ouml;&ouml;aasta puhkusega v&otilde;i antakse j&auml;rgmise t&ouml;&ouml;aasta kestel m&otilde;nel muul ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Portion of holiday which was not used due to the interruption of the holiday shall be granted at another time during the same working year by agreement of the parties, added to the holiday of the following year or granted at another time during the following working year. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui pooled ei ole saavutanud kokkulepet puhkuse katkestamise t&otilde;ttu kasutamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkuse v&otilde;i selle osa &uuml;leviimise kohta, on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus j&auml;&auml;da puhkusele kasutamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkusep&auml;evade ulatuses, teatades sellest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kirjalikult ette kaks n&auml;dalat. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If parties have not reached an agreement on transfer of a holiday or a portion of the holiday which was not used due to the interruption of the holiday, the employee has the right to go on holiday to the extent of the unused holiday days and he or she shall notify the employer thereof in writing at least two weeks in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmise vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalising grant of holidays </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkus vormistatakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Holidays are formalised pursuant to the procedure established by the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusetasu ja kasutamata puhkuse rahaline h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday Pay and Monetary Compensation for Unused Holiday </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusetasu </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday pay </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hi- ja lisapuhkuse aja eest maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;tajale puhkusetasu, mille arvutamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>Employers shall pay employees holiday pay for annual holiday and additional holiday, which are calculated pursuant to the procedure established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusetasu maksmine </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of holiday pay </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Puhkusetasu makstakse t&auml;ies ulatuses hiljemalt eelviimasel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval enne puhkuse algust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Holiday pay is paid in full not later than on the penultimate working day before commencement of the holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja, kellele ei makstud puhkusetasu k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 3 etten&auml;htud ajal, v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda puhkuse pikendamist puhkusetasu maksmisega viivitatud aja v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employee who is not paid holiday pay at the time prescribed in subsections (1) or (3) of this section may demand extension of his or her holiday with payment of holiday pay for the period of time the holiday pay is delayed. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kollektiivlepingus s&auml;testatud tingimustel v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 4 ja 5 ning &sect; 10 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale maksta puhkusetasu kahes osas, kusjuures v&auml;hemalt pool puhkusetasu makstakse hiljemalt eelviimasel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval enne puhkuse algust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Under the conditions provided for in a collective agreement, holiday pay may be paid to an employee specified in clauses 9 (2) 4) and 5) and subsection 10 (1) in two parts, and at least half of the holiday pay shall be paid not later than on the penultimate working day before commencement of the holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>Teine osa puhkusetasu makstakse v&auml;lja kollektiivlepingus kokkulepitud ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>The other portion of the holiday pay shall be paid at the time agreed in the collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Kasutamata puhkuse h&uuml;vitamine t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu v&otilde;i teenistussuhte l&otilde;ppemise korral </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for unused holidays upon termination of employment contract or service relationship </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu v&otilde;i teenistussuhete l&otilde;ppemise korral on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale maksma kasutamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkuse eest rahalist h&uuml;vitist, kuid kokku mitte rohkem kui nelja aasta kasutamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkuse eest. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the termination of an employment contract or a service relationship, the employer is required to pay the employee monetary compensation for unused holidays, but for not more than a total of four years' unused holidays. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusetasu maksmine riigieelarve vahenditest </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of holiday pay from state budget funds </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigieelarve vahenditest Sotsiaalministeeriumi eelarve kaudu makstakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following shall be financed from the state budget funds through the budget of the Ministry of Social Affairs: </inglise>
<eesti>1) puhkusetasu ja kasutamata puhkuse rahalist h&uuml;vitist 28 kalendrip&auml;eva &uuml;letava puhkuseosa eest vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ike 2 punktidele 1 ja 2 alaealistele ja isikutele, kellele on m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension v&otilde;i rahvapension t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the holiday pay and monetary compensation for unused holidays of minors and persons who are granted a pension for incapacity for work or the national pension on the basis of incapacity for work, for holidays of more than twenty-eight calendar days pursuant to clauses 9 (2) 1) and 2) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) puhkusetasu k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 30 s&auml;testatud t&auml;iendava lapsepuhkuse eest. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the holiday pay for the additional child care leave provided for in &sect; 30 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1 ja 2 toodud puhkusetasu ja h&uuml;vitised maksab v&auml;lja t&ouml;&ouml;andja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The holiday pay and compensations set out in clauses (1) 1) and 2) of this section shall be paid by the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis etten&auml;htud puhkusetasu ja h&uuml;vitise suuruse ning maksmise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The holiday pay and the amount of the compensation prescribed in this section and the procedure for payment shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Vanemapuhkused </eesti>
<inglise>Leaves for Parents </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Pregnancy leave and maternity leave </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Naisele antakse s&uuml;nnituslehe alusel rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkust 126 kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Based on a certificate for maternity leave, a woman shall be granted a pregnancy and maternity leave of 126 calendar days. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Mitmikute s&uuml;nni v&otilde;i t&uuml;sistustega s&uuml;nnituse korral antakse rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkust 140 kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of a multiple birth or a delivery with complications, a pregnancy and maternity leave of 140 calendar days shall be granted. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkus algab v&auml;hemalt 56 kalendrip&auml;eva enne arsti m&auml;&auml;ratud oodatavat s&uuml;nnituse t&auml;htaega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A pregnancy and maternity leave shall start at least fifty-six calendar days before the due date for delivery as established by a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkuse aja eest makstakse h&uuml;vitist vastavalt Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseadusele (RT 1991, 23, 272; RT I 1999, 7, 113; 29, 397; 2000, 57, 374; 84, 536; 102, 675). </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Compensation for the period of pregnancy leave and maternity leave shall be paid pursuant to the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act (RT 1991, 23, 272; RT I 1999, 7, 113; 29, 397; 2000, 57, 374; 84, 536; 102, 675). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsendaja puhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Adoptive parents leave </inglise>
<eesti>Alla 4-aastase lapse lapsendajale antakse puhkust 70 kalendrip&auml;eva, alates lapsendamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>An adoptive parent of a child of under 4 years of age shall be granted a leave of seventy calendar days, as of the date of adoption. </inglise>
<eesti>Selle aja eest makstakse h&uuml;vitist vastavalt Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseadusele. </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation hall be paid for this period of time pursuant to the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsehoolduspuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Parental leave </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lapse emale v&otilde;i isale antakse tema soovil lapsehoolduspuhkust kuni 3-aastase lapse kasvatamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A mother or father shall be granted parental leave at his or her request for raising a child of up to 3 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsehoolduspuhkus l&otilde;peb hiljemalt lapse 3-aastaseks saamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgneval p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>A parental leave terminates not later than on the day which follows the day on which the child reaches 3 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui ema v&otilde;i isa ei kasuta lapsehoolduspuhkust, v&otilde;ib puhkuse anda lapse tegelikule hooldajale, kes seaduslikul alusel elab Eesti Vabariigis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a mother or father does not use a parental leave, the leave may be granted to the actual caregiver of the child who lawfully resides in the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lapsehoolduspuhkust v&otilde;ib kasutada &uuml;hes osas v&otilde;i osade kaupa igal ajal kuni 3-aastase lapse kasvatamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Parental leave may be used in one part or in parts at any time for raising a child of up to 3 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Lapsehoolduspuhkust ei anta, kui laps elab sotsiaalhoolekandeasutuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Parental leave shall not be granted if the child lives in a social welfare institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Lapsehoolduspuhkuse ajaks t&ouml;&ouml;leping v&otilde;i teenistussuhe peatub ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajale makstakse selle aja eest lapsehooldustasu vastavalt riiklike peretoetuste seadusele (RT I 1997, 42, 676; 77, 1309; 1998, 86/87, 1407; 1999, 10, 150; 16, 273; 67, 657; 82, 749; 2000, 102, 668). </eesti>
<inglise>(5) For the duration of parental leave, an employment contract or service relationship shall be suspended and the employee shall be paid child care allowance pursuant to the State Family Benefits Act (RT I 1997, 42, 676; 77, 1309; 1998, 86/87, 1407; 1999, 10, 150; 16, 273; 67, 657; 82, 749; 2000, 102, 668). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iendav lapsepuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Additional child care leave </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isal on &otilde;igus saada ema rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkuse ajal v&otilde;i kahe kuu jooksul p&auml;rast lapse s&uuml;ndi 14 kalendrip&auml;eva t&auml;iendavat lapsepuhkust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A father has the right to be granted an additional child care leave of fourteen calendar days during the pregnancy leave or maternity leave of the mother or within two months after the birth of the child. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Emale v&otilde;i isale antakse tema soovil igal t&ouml;&ouml;aastal t&auml;iendavat lapsepuhkust: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A mother or father shall be granted an additional child care leave every working year at his or her request as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kolm kalendrip&auml;eva, kui tal on &uuml;ks v&otilde;i kaks alla 14-aastast last; </eesti>
<inglise>1) child care leave of three calendar days if the mother or father has one or two children under 14 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kuus kalendrip&auml;eva, kui tal on kolm v&otilde;i enam alla 14-aastast last v&otilde;i v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks alla 3-aastane laps. </eesti>
<inglise>2) child care leave of six calendar days if the mother or father has three or more children under 14 years of age or at least one child under 3 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 1 ja 2 nimetatud puhkusele on &otilde;igus ka lapse eestkostjal, kes kasvatab last ilma vanemateta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A guardian raising a child without parents is also entitled to the leave specified in clauses (2) 1) and 2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Lapse 3-aastaseks ning 14-aastaseks saamise aastal antakse t&auml;iendav lapsepuhkus, olenemata sellest, kas lapse s&uuml;nnip&auml;ev on enne v&otilde;i p&auml;rast puhkust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An additional child care leave shall be granted in the year that a child reaches 3 years of age and 14 years of age regardless of whether the child's birthday is before or after the leave. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&auml;iendav lapsepuhkus liidetakse p&otilde;hi- ja lisapuhkusele, samuti pikendatud p&otilde;hipuhkusele ja antakse sellega koos v&otilde;i poolte kokkuleppel m&otilde;nel muul ajal samal t&ouml;&ouml;aastal. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An additional child care leave shall be added to an annual holiday, additional holiday or extended annual holiday and shall be granted together with the same or, by agreement of the parties, at another time during the same working year. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&auml;iendavat lapsepuhkust ei anta, kui laps elab sotsiaalhoolekandeasutuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An additional child care leave shall not be granted if the child lives in a social welfare institution. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iendav palgata lapsepuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Additional child care leave without pay </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja soovil andma t&auml;iendavat palgata lapsepuhkust: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) At the request of the employee, the employer is required to grant an additional child care leave without pay to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kuni 14-aastast last kasvatavale lapsevanemale, samuti eestkostjale v&otilde;i hooldajale, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud sotsiaalhoolekande seaduse (RT I 1995, 21, 323; 1996, 49, 953; 1997, 35, 538; 77, 1309; 2000, 33, 198) &sect; 15 l&otilde;ike 2 alusel kirjalik perekonnas hooldamise leping; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a parent who is raising a child of 14 years of age, and a guardian or caregiver with whom a written foster care contract has been entered into pursuant to subsection 15 (2) of the Social Welfare Act (RT I 1995, 21, 323; 1996, 49, 953; 1997, 35, 538; 77, 1309; 2000, 33, 198); </inglise>
<eesti>2) kuni 18-aastast puudega last kasvatavale lapsevanemale, samuti eestkostjale v&otilde;i hooldajale, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud sotsiaalhoolekande seaduse &sect; 15 l&otilde;ike 2 alusel kirjalik perekonnas hooldamise leping. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a parent who is raising a disabled child under the age of 18, and a guardian or caregiver with whom a written foster care contract has been entered into pursuant to subsection 15 (2) of the Social Welfare Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&auml;iendavat palgata lapsepuhkust antakse kuni 14 kalendrip&auml;eva t&ouml;&ouml;aasta kestel poolte kokkuleppega m&auml;&auml;ratud ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An additional child care leave without pay shall be granted for up to fourteen calendar days during a working year at a time established by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Palgata ja osaliselt tasustatav puhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday without Pay or with Partial Pay </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgata puhkus poolte kokkuleppel </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday without pay by agreement of parties </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&otilde;ib tema soovil anda palgata puhkust poolte kokkuleppega m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>Employees may be granted a holiday without pay at their request for a period of time established by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Osaliselt tasustatav puhkus t&ouml;&ouml;andja ettepanekul </eesti>
<inglise>Partially paid holiday on proposal of employer </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;mahu v&otilde;i tellimuste ajutisel v&auml;henemisel v&otilde;ib poolte kokkuleppel ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekul anda t&ouml;&ouml;tajale osaliselt tasustatavat puhkust kuni kolmeks kuuks, teatades sellest t&ouml;&ouml;tajale kirjalikult ette v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon a temporary decrease in the volume of work or orders, employees may be granted a partially paid holiday for up to three months by agreement of the parties and with the approval of the labour inspector of the employer's location (residence), and the employees shall be notified thereof in writing at least two months in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Osaliselt tasustatava puhkuse ajal makstav puhkusetasu ei v&otilde;i olla v&auml;iksem kui 60 protsenti Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud palga alamm&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The holiday pay payable during holidays with partial pay shall not be less than 60 per cent of the minimum salary rate established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;korralduse muudatusega mitten&otilde;ustumise korral on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;andjapoolse t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu tingimuste rikkumise t&otilde;ttu t&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petada Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In case an employee disagrees with changes in work organisation specified in subsection (1) of this section, he or she has the right to terminate the employment contract due to violation of the conditions of the employment contract by the employer pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja saadab t&ouml;&ouml;taja osaliselt tasustatavale puhkusele ilma t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekuta, siis on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud maksma h&uuml;vitust saamata j&auml;&auml;nud palga suuruses. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an employer orders an employee to take a holiday with partial pay without the consent of the employee or the labour inspector, the employer is required to pay compensation to the employee in the amount of unpaid wages. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgata puhkuse andmise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Duty to grant holiday without pay </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja soovil andma palgata puhkust: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) At the request of an employee, the employer is required to grant a holiday without pay to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;tajale g&uuml;mnaasiumi riigieksamite ning kutse&otilde;ppeasutuse, rakendusliku k&otilde;rgkooli v&otilde;i &uuml;likooli sisseastumiseksamite sooritamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an employee for taking the state examinations of an upper secondary school or the entrance examinations of a vocational educational institution, institution of applied higher education or a university; </inglise>
<eesti>2) muudel seaduse, muu &otilde;igusakti, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>2) in other cases prescribed by law, other legislation, a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) G&uuml;mnaasiumi riigieksamite ning kutse&otilde;ppeasutuse, rakendusliku k&otilde;rgkooli v&otilde;i &uuml;likooli sisseastumiseksamite sooritamiseks antakse palgata puhkust &otilde;ppeasutuse teatise alusel selles n&auml;idatud ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Holidays without pay shall be granted for taking the state examinations of an upper secondary school or the entrance examinations of a vocational educational institution, institution of applied higher education or a university on the basis of a statement from the educational institution for the time indicated therein. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudel juhtudel antakse palgata puhkust vastavas seaduses, muus &otilde;igusaktis, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>In other cases, holidays without pay shall be granted to the extent prescribed in the corresponding Act, other legislation, a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgata puhkuse vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalisation of holiday without pay </inglise>
<eesti>Palgata puhkus vormistatakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Holidays without pay shall be formalised pursuant to the procedure established by the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>State Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>State supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide t&auml;itmise &uuml;le teostab T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) State supervision over compliance with this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof shall be exercised by the Labour Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhatajal ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektoril on &otilde;igus teha ettekirjutusi k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide rikkumise korral ning kontrollida ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of violation of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof, the head of a regional office of the Labour Inspectorate and labour inspectors of the location (residence) of employers have the right to issue precepts and inspect compliance with the precepts. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja ja t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutused on t&ouml;&ouml;andjale t&auml;itmiseks kohustuslikud. </eesti>
<inglise>Precepts issued by the head of a regional office of the Labour Inspectorate and labour inspectors are mandatory for employers. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettekirjutuse vaidlustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Contestation of precept </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja ei n&otilde;ustu oma asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutusega, on tal &otilde;igus esitada kas T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhatajale v&otilde;i halduskohtule kaebus ettekirjutuse saamise p&auml;evast arvates k&uuml;mne kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an employer does not agree with a precept issued by a labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer, the employer has the right to file a complaint either with the head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate or an administrative court within ten calendar days after the date of receipt of the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ettekirjutuse on teinud T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja, on t&ouml;&ouml;andjal ettekirjutusega mitten&otilde;ustumise korral &otilde;igus esitada kaebus kas T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni peadirektorile v&otilde;i halduskohtule ettekirjutuse saamise p&auml;evast arvates k&uuml;mne kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>If a precept is issued by the head of a regional office of the Labour Inspectorate and an employer does not agree with the precept, the employer has the right to file a complaint either with the Director General of the Labour Inspectorate or an administrative court within ten calendar days after the date of receipt of the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaebuse esitamine ei vabasta kohustusest ettekirjutust t&auml;ita. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The filing of a complaint does not discharge the person from the obligation to comply with the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhatajal, T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni peadirektoril v&otilde;i halduskohtul on &otilde;igus kaebuse esitaja taotlusel v&otilde;i omal algatusel peatada ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmine kuni kaebuse lahendamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The head of a regional office of the Labour Inspectorate, the Director General of the Labour Inspectorate or an administrative court has the right to suspend compliance with a precept until adjudication of the complaint at the request of the complainant or on its own initiative. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja v&otilde;i T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni peadirektor vaatab kaebuse l&auml;bi ning kaebuse saamise p&auml;evast arvates &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul otsustab, kas j&auml;tta ettekirjutus j&otilde;usse, see muuta v&otilde;i t&uuml;histada. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate or the Director General of the Labour Inspectorate shall review the complaint and decide, within one week after the date of receipt of the complaint, whether the precept remains in force, is amended or revoked. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus tehakse kaebuse esitajale teatavaks allkirja vastu v&otilde;i saadetakse posti teel v&auml;ljastusteatega. </eesti>
<inglise>The complainant shall be notified of the decision against his or her signature or the decision shall be sent to him or her by post with advice of delivery. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kaebuse esitaja T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja v&otilde;i T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni peadirektori otsusega ei n&otilde;ustu, v&otilde;ib ta selle vaidlustada halduskohtus. </eesti>
<inglise>If the complainant does not agree with the decision of the head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate or the Director General of the Labour Inspectorate, the complainant may contest it in an administrative court. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
